content:
Human trafficking is not far from us. Even if you don't go to Thailand, you may still be trafficked in China, and the police may not file a case.
In 23 years, the Thai police said that nearly 200 Chinese were trafficked from Thailand to Myawaddy, Myanmar every day. Myawaddy Town is the second largest human trafficking center in Southeast Asia.
At the same time, according to the help documents established by the families of trafficked people, roughly more than half of the human trafficking incidents occurred in Yunnan and Guangxi, especially Xishuangbanna.
There are quite a few cases of help seeking, where the family members called the police but the police did not file a case.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
The University of Michigan in the United States has terminated its cooperation with Shanghai Jiao Tong University on the grounds of national security.
The University of Michigan announced on its official website on January 10 that its president, Ono Mitsuo, made this decision on Friday, ending the 20-year academic cooperation between the two schools.
U.S. House of Representatives member Mullner said that the joint college of the University of Michigan and Jiaotong University is helping China achieve military modernization. Last October, five Chinese students who went to the University of Michigan through an exchange program were eventually found to be engaged in intelligence activities at Camp Grayling.
The University of Michigan is the third American university in the past five months to terminate cooperation with Chinese universities due to national security risks raised by the ad hoc committee. Last fall, Georgia Institute of Technology announced the termination of cooperation with Georgia Institute of Technology Shenzhen Institute, and the University of California, Berkeley also terminated cooperation with Tsinghua University.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Following the announcement by the University of Macau on its official website that starting from the 2025/2026 school year, non-college entrance examination candidates from the mainland will no longer be eligible to apply for the university's undergraduate courses, four Macau universities including the Macau University of Science and Technology and the Macau Polytechnic University have recently followed suit and announced that they will no longer enroll non-college entrance examination candidates from the mainland in the 2025/2026 school year. Mainland students will no longer be able to apply to these five universities in Macau through international curriculum system scores such as A-Level/AP/IB. Industry insiders analyzed that the adjustment of policies by several universities in Macau may be related to the frequent academic fraud incidents in Hong Kong and Macau in recent years. According to the Ta Kung Pao, the Macau University of Science and Technology earlier discovered that 24 mainland students used forged DSE scores to enroll. After verification, the school made decisions such as revoking their student status and reporting to the police.

Japan on Wednesday (January 8) linked more than 200 cyber attacks on Japan's national security and high-tech data in the past five years to the Chinese hacker group "Mirror", detailed their attack methods, and called on government agencies and companies to strengthen preventive measures.
The Japanese National Police Agency said that those attacked by Mirror included the Japanese Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the Ministry of Defense, the Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency, and politicians, journalists, private companies and think tanks related to advanced technology.
In response, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs said that "making relevant judgments based solely on the targets and methods of hacker attacks is neither professional nor responsible."
